Themba Godi’s African People’s Convention (APC) party launches its election manifesto in Mninginisi village, outside Giyani this Saturday. Godi says APC is the only party that is launching its Manifesto in rural areas. Supporters of the African People’s Convention are starting to arrive at Mninginisi. Party leader, Themba Godi is expected to address supporters on his plan ahead of the general elections. Residents of the village say they hope Godi will provide solutions for challenges such as water shortages and road infrastructure. “We support Themba Godi because we believe he can better our lives. We need roads, water and better education facilities for our children. We are struggling in this village and we believe Themba Godi can help us with our challenges.”  